<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-456] ProducerSendThread calls ListBuffer.size a whole bunch. That is a O(n) operation</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-456</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hi all,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So there are various statements throughout the async code that call &apos;events.size&apos;, mostly for debugging purposes.&lt;br/&gt;
Problem is that this call is O&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/thumbs_down.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;, so it could add up if the batch size is high. (it&apos;s a ListBuffer)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I see this in at least ProducerSendThread (x4), likely more. Will factor this out myself soon when I start hacking on the project, just wanted to put this somewhere.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
