                            <comment id="13469338" author="mumrah" created="Thu, 4 Oct 2012 12:59:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I looked around in other parts of the code for similar situations (lots of calls to ListBuffer#size), didn&apos;t see any that were unnecessary.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the worst case, this saves two calls to size(); in the common case, it saves one call.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13469351" author="mumrah" created="Thu, 4 Oct 2012 13:02:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Only compatible with 0.8&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13469530" author="junrao" created="Thu, 4 Oct 2012 17:30:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the patch. Committed to 0.8.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This performance issue seems to have been fixed in scala 2.9.1.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.scala-lang.org/browse/SI-4933&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://issues.scala-lang.org/browse/SI-4933&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13469560" author="jkreps" created="Thu, 4 Oct 2012 18:02:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Why not just make this an ArrayBuffer so that there are 0 O&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/thumbs_down.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; operations? I suspect the ListBuffer thing was just a misunderstanding of scala collections underlying implementation (i.e. ListBuffer != ArrayList).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
